PLACEHOLDER — this is a scaffold. The final license text must be reviewed and set by
the founder before any public publication. The intended model is a fair-code
Sustainable Use License, matching n8n's own license: the source is available, free for
internal business and non-commercial use, but may not be offered as a competing hosted
or commercial service. This is NOT an OSI-approved open-source license; describe the
project as "fair-code / source-available", never "open source".

Scope of this license: the engine/, server/, dashboard/, and deploy/ directories.
The node/ directory (the n8n community node) is licensed separately under MIT — see
node/LICENSE — because n8n's verified-community-node program requires an MIT license.

The paid features (fix suggestions and auto-fixing) are NOT in this repository; they are
served from the Pisama cloud and are not covered by this license.

